  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nRight now, it appears that `forge install` clones the entire history of the git submodules.\r\n\r\nBut what we actually need is just the latest commit or a particular commit.\r\n\r\nIf possible, we can make it clone only the relevant commit. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.blog/2020-12-21-get-up-to-speed-with-partial-clone-and-shallow-clone/\r\n\r\nOf course, we will still need to clone all the dependencies recursively.\r\n\r\n\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
